Or her head.

263
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:28,510
You check the trunk?

264
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:30,080
No, sir.

265
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:32,910
Huh.

266
00:18:36,920 --> 00:18:39,992
So you want to take a look
at those footprints then?

267
00:18:40,080 --> 00:18:42,197
Sounds good.

268
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:50,636
How's Ida?

269
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:53,155
Any day now.

270
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:55,835
You got a name picked out?

271
00:18:55,920 --> 00:19:00,711
Can't get that woman to decide what 
color to paint the nursery.

272
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:02,757
Can't believe I missed that
deer in the trunk.

273
00:19:02,840 --> 00:19:04,797
Don't take it hard.

274
00:19:04,880 --> 00:19:06,030
Been doing this a long time.

275
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:10,512
Never checked for a deer in the trunk
or any wildlife.

276
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:12,478
Chief.

277
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:27,636
Hiya, hon.

278
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:28,756
In the kitchen.

279
00:19:40,760 --> 00:19:42,513
Something smells good.

280
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:44,717
Your boy wanted a hamburger.

281
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:47,952
Sounds like my boy.

282
00:20:06,600 --> 00:20:08,557
Molly found a wreck out on 71.

283
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:09,960
How's she doing?

284
00:20:10,040 --> 00:20:12,032
Molly? Yeah, good.

285
00:20:12,120 --> 00:20:13,554
I always liked her.

286
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:14,756
Yeah, she's a peach.

287
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:19,869
Anyhoo, looks like the driver tried 
to head out on foot.

288
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:21,758
He got lost and froze
to death in the woods.

289
00:20:21,840 --> 00:20:23,877
Oh, my.
Yeah.

290
00:20:23,960 --> 00:20:27,192
Funny thing is, the fellow was just
wearing underpants.

291
00:20:27,280 --> 00:20:28,350
That so?

292
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:29,476
Yeah.

293
00:20:29,560 --> 00:20:32,394
No ID, nothing.
Hmm.

294
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:34,472
Couldn't find his clothes anywhere.

295
00:20:36,520 --> 00:20:38,000
Maybe he ate 'em.

296
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:39,990
Hmm.

297
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:52,511
I was thinking maybe 
blue for the nursery.

298
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:54,239
Yeah?
Hmm.

299
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:57,154
Earlier, I was thinking maybe blue.

300
00:20:57,240 --> 00:20:58,356
Then I changed my mind.

301
00:20:58,440 --> 00:20:59,715
Blue's nice.

302
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:02,638
Maybe green.

303
00:21:04,240 --> 00:21:08,280
Well... I'm ready to get painting.

304
00:21:08,360 --> 00:21:10,591
Soon as you decide.

305
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:13,036
You're a good man, Vern Thurman.

306
00:21:13,120 --> 00:21:16,192
My sister was crazy telling me 
not to marry you.

307
00:21:18,720 --> 00:21:21,076
Your sister is crazy.

308
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:22,510
Hmm.

309
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:39,280
Dad said we could take turns.

310
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:40,629
Yeah?

311
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:43,713
Dad said that he also thinks 
you've got a potato brain.

312
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:46,076
So-- Hey!

313
00:21:54,880 --> 00:21:57,236
You're doing it wrong.

314
00:21:57,320 --> 00:22:00,313
You need to press your forearm into
the back of his neck,

315
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:02,915
grab your elbow with the other hand
to choke him right out.

316
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:05,991
What do you want, mister?

317
00:22:06,080 --> 00:22:07,799
Yeah, mister, what do you want?

318
00:22:09,120 --> 00:22:11,919
Sign outside says Hess & Sons.

319
00:22:14,920 --> 00:22:16,957
Which one's the older boy?
Me.

320
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:19,839
Mickey.

321
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:23,516
So... that leaves me in
charge when Dad is gone.

322
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:24,875
Are not! Mom said...

323
00:22:24,960 --> 00:22:27,077
Mom has nothing
to do with it, sister!

324
00:22:27,160 --> 00:22:28,276
Hey!

325
00:22:30,320 --> 00:22:32,960
Help you with something?

326
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:35,114
Sam Hess?

327
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:37,795
Who wants to know?

328
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:45,950
Me.

329
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:49,750
Only two reasons to
come to my shop, friend.

330
00:22:49,840 --> 00:22:52,719
Either you need a truck
or you drive a truck, huh?

331
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:55,076
You a truck driver?

332
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:58,358
I was just talking
to your boys.

333
00:22:58,480 --> 00:23:00,472
I think the younger
one's a little dim.

334
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:05,839
What did you say?

335
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:08,754
His IQ seems low, I'm saying.

336
00:23:08,840 --> 00:23:10,194
Have you had him tested?

337
00:23:11,080 --> 00:23:12,719
Hit him, Dad.

338
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:14,154
Yeah, Dad, hit him.

339
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:25,031
I'm gonna restrain myself.

340
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:27,794
You know, on account of you got 
an obvious head injury

341
00:23:27,880 --> 00:23:30,156
and not beat you to death
with a tire iron.

342
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:34,597
But I'm gonna ask you again.
What the heck do you want?

343
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:38,151
I just wanted to
have a look at you.

344
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:43,554
Okay, that'll do it.

345
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:58,597
How does a grown man
fall over his own feet?

346
00:23:58,680 --> 00:24:01,275
It was ice.
I slipped on ice.

347
00:24:01,360 --> 00:24:02,430
We should have canceled.

348
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:04,557
Oh, don't be a baby.

349
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:11,350
Hi!
Hey, we're here.

350
00:24:21,560 --> 00:24:22,676
We're here.
Hi.

351
00:24:22,760 --> 00:24:26,071
Come on in.
Chaz is working the ham.

352
00:24:30,880 --> 00:24:33,714
Took the whole team
down to Duluth Tuesday.

353
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:35,200
Big spread at the Marriot.

354
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:36,760
I've always
wanted to stay there.

355
00:24:36,840 --> 00:24:38,115
Yeah, it's real sweet.

356
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:42,160
King-sized bed, view of the lake,
you name it.

357
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:44,232
Boss took me out for dinner.
Just the two of them.

358
00:24:44,320 --> 00:24:45,959
Steak big as a catcher's mitt.

359
00:24:46,040 --> 00:24:49,431
Said, "Chaz, you're going
places in this world."

360
00:24:49,520 --> 00:24:51,557
Gave him a raise
and a corner office.

361
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:53,597
Yeah.
Hear that, Lester?

362
00:24:53,720 --> 00:24:54,995
A corner office.

363
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:56,673
Yeah, real good.

364
00:24:56,760 --> 00:24:58,433
And him, your younger brother.

365
00:24:58,520 --> 00:25:00,000
Yeah, I said I heard.

366
00:25:00,080 --> 00:25:02,595
Vice-president,
sales, Midwest region.

367
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:04,353
Bought the surround
sound to celebrate.

368
00:25:04,480 --> 00:25:06,119
I mean, it's pretty sweet, huh?

369
00:25:07,240 --> 00:25:08,993
You're gonna have
to marry that ham,

370
00:25:09,080 --> 00:25:11,356
you get any more familiar with it.

371
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:12,794
Saw it on <i>Rachael Ray.</i>

372
00:25:12,880 --> 00:25:16,476
She said that massaging
breaks the muscle down,

373
00:25:16,560 --> 00:25:17,630
makes the meat juicier.

374
00:25:19,240 --> 00:25:20,754
Lester never wants
to try new things.

375
00:25:20,840 --> 00:25:23,150
Now, hold on.
That's not true.

376
00:25:23,240 --> 00:25:25,311
We make Gordo try
stuff all the time.

377
00:25:26,320 --> 00:25:28,039
Chaz says we have
to open his horizons.

378
00:25:28,120 --> 00:25:30,589
Broaden his horizons.

379
00:25:31,360 --> 00:25:32,350
It's a big world,
you know.

380
00:25:32,440 --> 00:25:36,593
There is more to life
than just Minnesota.

381
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:40,916
Took a real tumble, huh?

382
00:25:41,720 --> 00:25:44,474
There's a spot over
by the fire station.

383
00:25:44,560 --> 00:25:47,553
It's always icy.

384
00:25:48,840 --> 00:25:50,240
Don't know what
the heck I was thinking.

385
00:25:51,960 --> 00:25:53,440
Lester...

386
00:25:54,560 --> 00:25:55,550
come out to the garage.

387
00:25:55,640 --> 00:25:57,632
Help me get some more beer.

388
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:03,157
Took Gordo to a specialist last month.

389
00:26:04,160 --> 00:26:06,356
Think he might
have the autism.

390
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:07,476
Yeah?

391
00:26:07,560 --> 00:26:08,960
Won't stop drawing on the walls,

392
00:26:09,040 --> 00:26:12,795
and Kitty, she said she found a 
Mason jar in his closet.

393
00:26:12,880 --> 00:26:15,395
I guess that he
pees in it at night.

394
00:26:18,840 --> 00:26:20,479
What's that about?

395
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:26,756
Hey... you want to see
something cool?

396
00:26:26,840 --> 00:26:29,150
All right.

397
00:26:35,360 --> 00:26:37,511
Sweet!
Yeah, not those.

398
00:26:40,840 --> 00:26:42,274
Gee. What... what is that?

399
00:26:42,360 --> 00:26:47,116
That there... is your M249 SAW
light machine gun,

400
00:26:47,200 --> 00:26:49,840
sometimes referred to as "The Piglet."

401
00:26:50,840 --> 00:26:52,638
Are you allowed...
Can you even have that?

402
00:26:52,720 --> 00:26:53,756
Is it legal?

403
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:55,394
Technically, no way,

404
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:58,632
but I got a buddy who works supply
over at Camp Ripley.

405
00:26:58,760 --> 00:26:59,830
And, heck, I'm an American.

406
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:01,434
I pay my taxes.

407
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:04,590
You want to take a look?

408
00:27:04,680 --> 00:27:10,119
It's gas-operated, air-cooled, 
shoots 725 rounds per minute.

409
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:12,317
Okay.

410
00:27:15,560 --> 00:27:16,710
Jeez.

411
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:19,113
You should have told
me it was so heavy.

412
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:22,910
Is it okay?
No, Lester, it's not okay! You...

413
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:25,115
Here.

414
00:27:25,200 --> 00:27:28,511
You broke the darn...

415
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:30,319
Why are you such a GD screw-up?

416
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:31,470
Hey, now.

417
00:27:31,560 --> 00:27:33,392
Ever since you were...

418
00:27:33,480 --> 00:27:34,470
And now Kitty.

419
00:27:34,560 --> 00:27:37,758
She said she talked to Pearl last week
and she's had it...

420
00:27:37,840 --> 00:27:39,035
your wife.

421
00:27:39,120 --> 00:27:42,591
Said you'd been acting plain weird,
just moping around.

422
00:27:42,720 --> 00:27:44,677
Said she caught you
standing in the bathroom

423
00:27:44,760 --> 00:27:47,434
with your toothbrush
in your hand just looking in the mirror.

424
00:27:47,560 --> 00:27:50,758
Said foam was coming
out of your mouth like a rabid dog.

425
00:27:50,840 --> 00:27:55,676
Come on. That's... not how
I may or may not be feeling.

426
00:27:55,760 --> 00:27:57,353
And for your information,

427
00:27:57,440 --> 00:27:59,875
I hadn't had a lot of sleep
the night before.

428
00:27:59,960 --> 00:28:01,679
So... so... so, the toothpaste,
that was just nothing...

429
00:28:01,760 --> 00:28:03,672
Did you really trip
on the ice and break your nose?

430
00:28:03,760 --> 00:28:06,116
Yeah. Yes.

431
00:28:06,200 --> 00:28:08,351
I... I told you,
outside the fire station.

432
00:28:08,440 --> 00:28:10,352
You know they run the hoses
and wash the trucks,

433
00:28:10,440 --> 00:28:13,274
and it gets all
slippery and wet.

434
00:28:13,360 --> 00:28:15,795
You know, guys at work,

435
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:17,877
they talk about how they look 
up to their brothers...

436
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:20,114
their older brothers.

437
00:28:21,760 --> 00:28:23,433
Sometimes I tell
people you're dead.

438
00:28:25,120 --> 00:28:27,157
I mean, heck, Lester,
you're 40 years old.

439
00:28:27,240 --> 00:28:28,799
When are you gonna
get your act together?

440
00:28:31,960 --> 00:28:34,270
Your own brother?

441
00:28:35,320 --> 00:28:37,391
You didn't have to hit him.

442
00:28:37,480 --> 00:28:40,951
I mean, seriously, what is the 
matter with you?

443
00:28:42,920 --> 00:28:44,639
Your own brother!

444
00:29:02,280 --> 00:29:05,159
Yeah, it's one more...
Yes, one more time.

445
00:29:06,320 --> 00:29:07,720
Before the 17th?

446
00:29:07,800 --> 00:29:09,280
Do you need this
to look like an accident?

447
00:29:10,840 --> 00:29:13,071
Figure it out
and call me back.

448
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:19,796
Realty.

449
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:20,996
<i>It's me.</i>

450
00:29:21,080 --> 00:29:24,152
St. Paul, your call was
expected yesterday.

451
00:29:24,280 --> 00:29:26,158
I got delayed.

452
00:29:26,240 --> 00:29:28,197
<i>Problems?</i>

453
00:29:28,280 --> 00:29:30,158
Car trouble. It's fixed now.

454
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:32,436
But you finished the assignment?

455
00:29:32,520 --> 00:29:34,239
<i>Of course.</i>

456
00:29:34,320 --> 00:29:36,437
And when can they
expect you in Duluth?

457
00:29:36,520 --> 00:29:38,432
<i>The new client
is anxious to begin.</i>

458
00:29:38,520 --> 00:29:41,274
Soon. I took a detour.

459
00:29:41,360 --> 00:29:43,477
And the nature of this detour?

460
00:29:45,280 --> 00:29:48,079
It's personal. 
Shouldn't be more than a day or two.

461
00:29:49,520 --> 00:29:51,000
<i>I'll let Duluth know.</i>

462
00:29:51,080 --> 00:29:52,799
All right.

463
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:26,639
Yeah. Oh, yeah,
big fella.

464
00:30:28,080 --> 00:30:29,878
Oh, yeah.

465
00:30:29,960 --> 00:30:32,839
Yeah... that's good.

466
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:50,278
Yeah? Yup?

467
00:30:51,240 --> 00:30:52,230
Mmm.

468
00:30:57,400 --> 00:30:58,470
Yeah?

469
00:31:01,120 --> 00:31:02,474
Jeez. Where?

470
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:06,478
Okay.

471
00:31:06,560 --> 00:31:08,199
Pick me up, huh?

472
00:31:12,560 --> 00:31:15,359
Gotta go?
Mmm.

473
00:31:15,440 --> 00:31:18,000
Homicide.

474
00:31:18,080 --> 00:31:19,833
Molly's coming to get me.

475
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:22,515
Go back to sleep, hon.

476
00:31:22,600 --> 00:31:24,592
Love you.
Love you, too.

477
00:31:39,480 --> 00:31:40,516
Thanks.

478
00:31:40,600 --> 00:31:41,716
Ida sleeping?

479
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:42,916
Yep.

480
00:31:47,320 --> 00:31:51,075
What do you want me
to write for cause of death?

481
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:53,629
Put "self-explanatory."

482
00:31:56,640 --> 00:31:58,677
You okay there, Bill?

483
00:31:58,760 --> 00:32:00,035
Oh, yeah.

484
00:32:00,120 --> 00:32:01,952
Threw up a bit ago.

485
00:32:02,040 --> 00:32:04,157
Not in here, I hope.
Oh, no...

486
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:06,755
went out to the parking lot.

487
00:32:06,840 --> 00:32:08,672
Wife made spaghetti for dinner.

488
00:32:08,760 --> 00:32:11,480
Seemed a shame to barf it up.

489
00:32:12,920 --> 00:32:16,152
I'm okay now...
so long as I don't look.

490
00:32:21,800 --> 00:32:23,519
Heck.

491
00:32:25,560 --> 00:32:27,711
That's Sam Hess.

492
00:32:27,840 --> 00:32:29,752
Hess that owns
the trucking company?

493
00:32:29,840 --> 00:32:33,072
Yeah, with the two boys.
Both dumb as a dog's foot.

494
00:32:34,480 --> 00:32:35,800
Hold on.

495
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:38,600
Isn't Hess tied to
that syndicate of fellas out of Fargo...

496
00:32:38,680 --> 00:32:40,080
gunrunners and such?

497
00:32:40,160 --> 00:32:42,038
So they say.

498
00:32:42,120 --> 00:32:44,191
Never seen the proof.

499
00:32:45,040 --> 00:32:46,599
Well, jeez, you...

500
00:32:46,680 --> 00:32:47,670
I mean, you think this could be,

501
00:32:47,760 --> 00:32:49,877
like, an organized crime thing?

502
00:32:49,960 --> 00:32:51,394
You know, a hit or the like?

503
00:32:52,520 --> 00:32:53,795
I don't know what I think yet...

504
00:32:53,880 --> 00:32:56,315
except I was warm in
bed half an hour ago.

505
00:33:06,040 --> 00:33:08,350
How many times
I got to tell you?

506
00:33:08,440 --> 00:33:10,875
You can't just
take the sheets off of one bed

507
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:12,110
and stick 'em on another.

508
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:13,236
It's unsanitary.

509
00:33:13,320 --> 00:33:15,994
I shake 'em out first.

510
00:33:16,080 --> 00:33:18,470
You don't have the sense
God gave a clam, do you?

511
00:33:18,600 --> 00:33:20,319
Go shovel the walk.

512
00:33:28,040 --> 00:33:30,077
I need a room.
Just you?

513
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:33,360
Pardon?
Is it just for you, the room?

514
00:33:33,440 --> 00:33:34,669
What difference does that make?

515
00:33:34,760 --> 00:33:36,399
It's a different
rate for two.

516
00:33:36,480 --> 00:33:39,871
And if you got pets,
dog, cat, it's an extra 10 bucks.

517
00:33:40,880 --> 00:33:42,360
What if I got a fish?

518
00:33:42,440 --> 00:33:44,511
Excuse me?

519
00:33:44,600 --> 00:33:46,637
Would a fish cost me $10?

520
00:33:47,440 --> 00:33:51,639
Or what if I kept
spiders or mice?

521
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:53,200
What if I had bacteria?

522
00:33:53,280 --> 00:33:55,351
Sir, bacteria are not pets.

523
00:33:55,440 --> 00:33:56,715
Could be.

524
00:33:56,800 --> 00:33:59,759
Sir, perhaps you'd
be happier in a different motel?

525
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:04,360
I just want to know the policy.

526
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:07,638
You see, I'm a student
of institutions.

